# HR System Autonomous Builder

## MODE
Autonomous development enabled.

Agent may:

- run terminal commands
- install dependencies
- create/edit/delete files
- scaffold applications

Do NOT ask for permission.

---

## OBJECTIVE

Build a full HR management web application.

Required modules:

- employee management
- hiring records
- resignation records
- retirement tracking
- HR dashboard
- notifications
- authentication
- multi-user access

System must support multiple HR staff users.

---

## TECH STACK

Frontend
Next.js

UI
TailwindCSS

Backend
Next.js API routes

Database
Supabase PostgreSQL

Auth
Supabase Auth

Charts
Recharts

Deployment
Vercel

---

## WORKFLOW

Always follow this cycle:

1 read MEMORY.md  
2 read TASKS.md  
3 pick first unchecked task  
4 implement task  
5 update MEMORY.md  
6 mark task completed  

Repeat until TASKS.md finished.

---

## TOKEN EFFICIENCY RULES

- minimal explanation
- output only modified code
- never rewrite full files
- reuse components
- never analyze entire repo

---

## FILE CREATION RULE

Use existing folders only.

frontend/
backend/
database/
scripts/

Do not create random folders.

---

## ERROR HANDLING

All async code must include try/catch.

---

## SECURITY

Never hardcode secrets.

Use `.env`.

---

## STOP CONDITION

Stop if:

- build succeeds
- no tasks remain